Since you own **synerydev.site**, you can absolutely create an email address like:

**`rushidaulatkar@synerydev.site`**

Here‚Äôs how it works on your Raspberry Pi mail server:

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Creating a Mailbox for `rushidaulatkar@synerydev.site`

### 1. Add a System User

Postfix + Dovecot can use normal Linux system users as mailboxes.
On your Pi, create a user:

```bash
sudo adduser rushidaulatkar
```

This will:

* Create a home directory `/home/rushidaulatkar`
* Create a mailbox at `/var/mail/rushidaulatkar`

Set a password (you‚Äôll use it in your email client like Thunderbird, Outlook, or on your phone).

---

### 2. Tell Postfix/Dovecot Where Mail Goes

By default:

* Incoming mail for `rushidaulatkar@synerydev.site` ‚Üí delivered to `/var/mail/rushidaulatkar` (or Maildir if configured).
* Dovecot will expose that mailbox over IMAP/POP3, so you can connect with an email app.

If you prefer **Maildir format** (better for IMAP), edit Postfix config:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/postfix/main.cf
```

Add:

```
home_mailbox = Maildir/
```

Then create a Maildir for the user:

```bash
sudo mkdir -p /home/rushidaulatkar/Maildir
sudo chown -R rushidaulatkar: /home/rushidaulatkar/Maildir
```

---

### 3. Access the Mailbox

Now you can configure an email client:

* **Username**: `rushidaulatkar` (or full email depending on config)
* **Password**: the one you set with `adduser`
* **IMAP server**: `mail.synerydev.site` (port 993, SSL/TLS)
* **SMTP server**: `mail.synerydev.site` (port 587, STARTTLS or SSL/TLS)

---

### 4. (Optional) Use Virtual Mailboxes

If you don‚Äôt want every email address to be a Linux system user, you can set up **virtual mailboxes** in Postfix/Dovecot.
That way you can create `rushidaulatkar@synerydev.site`, `info@synerydev.site`, etc., without needing separate Pi user accounts. (This is more advanced but better if you want multiple email accounts.)

---

‚úÖ So yes, you can definitely have `rushidaulatkar@synerydev.site` running on your Raspberry Pi ‚Äî it‚Äôll work like any other professional email address.
